<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsum of head with minute punctures, clypeus smooth with strong luster (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9B, C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus elevated, anterior margin narrowly and deeply incised; labrum small and triangle, long than broad; malar space 1.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of middle ocellus; postocellar area 2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long, middle furrow weak; lateral furrows distinct, slightly divergent backwards; POL: OOL: OCL = 3.5: 4: 6; head behind eyes weakly enlarged (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9B, C</figureCitation>
); antenna 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head breadth, club breadth 2.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
apical breadth of antennomere 3, club length 1.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of antennomere 3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9F</figureCitation>
), antennomere 3 as long as longest axis of eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesonotum very densely punctured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9D</figureCitation>
), mesopleuron densely and minutely punctured, interspaces between punctures microsculptured; mesoscutellum roundly elevated, without middle furrow; mesopleuron with a distinct oblique carina; cenchrus elliptical, distance between inner margin of cenchri 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longest axis of a cenchrus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal tergum 1 with minute punctures and microsculptures, other terga finely and densely microsculptured, ovipositor sheath largely smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9E, H</figureCitation>
). Tergum 1 with low but distinct lateral carina, anterior corner roundish; posterior margin very deeply and roundly incised (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9E</figureCitation>
); middle process of sternum 7 broad and triangular, basal breadth about 1/3 breadth of sternite 7; lance narrow and long, subapical annuli clearly broadened, total length of annuli 4.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height of 13th annulus, first annulus 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9K</figureCitation>
); lancet with 47 serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9K</figureCitation>
), middle serrulae weakly narrowed toward truncate apex, each side with 3-4 large subbasal teeth, distance between middle serrulae 1.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal breadth of serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Asicimbex lii Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B head in front view C head in dorsal view D thoracic notum E abdominal terga F antenna G mesopleuron and metapleuron H lateral side of abdomen I hind tarsus J claw K lancet L middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707232" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">9L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
